radiographic_examinations.findings: Minimal linear atelectasis in the lung bases, mild periportal edema, dilated appendix containing two appendicoliths with surrounding inflammatory stranding in the right lower quadrant, no extraluminal gas or evidence of perforation. The liver, spleen, pancreas, adrenals, gallbladder, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, aorta, uterus, adnexa, rectum, colon, and bones were evaluated and reported mostly normal with congenital nonunion or old fracture of the left transverse processes of L3 and L4.
